column124: Student is in designated/scheduled instructional arrangement and needed no more behavioral supports than peers.
Student is in the designated/scheduled instructional arrangement but needs behavior support to remain in the instructional setting.
Student's behavior has prevented them from being in the designated/scheduled instructional arrangement.
Will complete task/demand and request help as needed.
Stalls to begin task or gather appropriate materials, but will begin and complete task/demand, asking for help as needed.
Stalls demand and/or focuses on unassigned activities but will return to completing assigned task.
Displays non-compliance (ex. sits at desk without working, puts head down), engages in off task activities, and may return to, but will not complete, the assigned task.
Displays non-compliance (ex. sits at desk without working, puts head down), engages in off task activities, and will not begin or complete the assigned task.
